## Mandatory local validation

The online query creates only a candidate pool. Before selection, Lua must still verify:

1. The candidate has the exact reciprocal pairing ability.
2. A Doctor has exactly `Time Lord Doctor` as its creature types and no additional creature type.
3. Standalone `Partner` is not confused with any `Partner—...` or `Partner with ...` variant.
4. Candidate and first Commander do not share the same normalized name or Oracle ID.
5. Backgrounds are legendary Background enchantments.

## Updating

Recheck the queries when Wizards adds a partner variant or changes Oracle wording. Prefer generating any future static snapshot from Scryfall Oracle Cards bulk data; do not hand-maintain card names when a rules-derived query can express the pairing.
